37 ARTICLE 25.3. INDIANAPOLIS PUBLIC EDUCATION
38 CORPORATION
39 Chapter 1. Scope of Authority
40 Sec. 1. The Indianapolis public education corporation exists and
41 shall operate for the public purpose of establishing a unified
42 student transportation, school property, and school performance
HB 1423—LS 7118/DI 110

10
1 system within the geographic boundaries of the school city that
2 maximizes the efficient use of taxpayer provided resources,
3 respects the decision making of individual public schools and the
4 school city, and creates the best conditions for student learning and
5 success.
6 Sec. 2. This article shall be liberally construed to effect the
7 purposes of this article. If any other law or rule is inconsistent with
8 this article, this article is controlling as to the administration and
9 management of school property, transportation, and school
10 performance within the geographic boundaries of the school city
11 undertaken under this article.
12 Chapter 2. Definitions
13 Sec. 1. The definitions in:
14 (1) this chapter; and
15 (2) except as provided in section 2 of this chapter, IC 20-25-2;
16 apply throughout this article.
17 Sec. 2. "Board of school commissioners" refers to the board of
18 school commissioners established by IC 20-25-3-1.
19 Sec. 3. "Corporation" refers to the Indianapolis public
20 education corporation established by IC 20-25.3-3-1.
21 Sec. 4. "Corporation board" refers to the Indianapolis public
22 education corporation board established by IC 20-25.3-3-2.
23 Sec. 5. "Mayor" refers to the mayor of a consolidated city.
24 Sec. 6. "Participating school" means the following schools:
25 (1) A school maintained by the school city.
26 (2) The following that are located within the geographic
27 boundaries of the school city:
28 (A) A participating innovation network school.
29 (B) A participating innovation network charter school.
30 (C) A charter school.
31 Sec. 7. "School property" means a building or real property
32 that is:
33 (1) leased or owned by the school city or a participating
34 school; and
35 (2) located within the geographic boundaries of the school
36 city.
37 Chapter 3. Indianapolis Public Education Corporation
38 Sec. 1. There is established in a county containing a consolidated
39 city for the public purposes set forth in this article a distinct
40 municipal corporation to be known as the Indianapolis Public
41 Education Corporation.
42 Sec. 2. (a) The corporation is governed by the Indianapolis
HB 1423—LS 7118/DI 110

11
1 public education corporation board appointed under this section.
2 (b) The corporation board is comprised of the following nine (9)
3 members:
4 (1) Three (3) members appointed by the mayor who are
5 leaders of participating innovation network charter schools or
6 charter schools located within the geographic boundaries of
7 the school city.
8 (2) Three (3) members appointed by the mayor who are
9 members of the board of school commissioners.
10 (3) Three (3) members appointed by the mayor who have:
11 (A) expertise in management, capital planning, facilities,
12 transportation, or logistics; or
13 (B) experience in working with vulnerable student
14 populations and communities.
15 (c) All members of the corporation board must reside within the
16 geographic boundaries of the school city.
17 (d) The mayor shall appoint one (1) of the members of the
18 corporation board as chairperson of the corporation board.
19 Sec. 3. (a) The term of office of an appointed member of the
20 corporation board is six (6) years. The member's term begins on
21 July 1 after the appointment.
22 (b) Each member holds office for the term of appointment and
23 continues to serve after expiration of the appointment until a
24 successor is appointed and qualified. A member is eligible for
25 reappointment.
26 (c) If there is a vacancy in the corporation board, the mayor
27 shall fill the vacancy for the unexpired term.
28 (d) A vacancy occurs if a member dies, resigns, changes
29 residence of the county, or ceases to be a:
30 (1) leader of a participating innovation network charter
31 school or charter school located within the geographic
32 boundaries of the school city; or
33 (2) member of the board of commissioners.
34 (e) A member of the corporation board may be removed for
35 cause by the mayor.
36 Sec. 4. (a) A majority of the corporation board members
37 constitutes a quorum for a meeting. The corporation board may
38 act by an affirmative vote of a majority of the corporation board.
39 (b) A vacancy in the membership of the corporation board does
40 not impair the right of a quorum to exercise all rights and perform
41 all duties of the corporation board.
42 Sec. 5. Meetings of the members of the corporation board shall
