1 be held at the call of the chairperson. The members shall meet at
2 least once every three (3) months to attend to the business of the
3 corporation.
4 Sec. 6. The members of the corporation board are not entitled
5 to any salary, per diem, or other reimbursements or compensation
6 to serve on the corporation board.
7 Sec. 7. The corporation board shall keep the corporation
8 board's documents in the office of the corporation or in an
9 electronic format. The corporation board shall record the aye and
10 nay vote on the final passage of any item of business and on any
11 other item if two (2) corporation board members request that the
12 votes be recorded by ayes and nays.
13 Sec. 8. (a) The corporation board shall adopt rules of procedure
14 for corporation board meetings. The corporation board may
15 suspend the rules of procedure by unanimous vote of the members
16 present at the meeting. The corporation board shall not suspend
17 the rules of procedure beyond the duration of the meeting at which
18 the suspension of rules occurs.
19 (b) The corporation board may exercise the powers to supervise
20 internal affairs common to municipal legislative and
21 administrative bodies.
22 Sec. 9. The corporation board shall exercise the executive and
23 legislative powers of the corporation.
24 Sec. 10. (a) The corporation board shall appoint an individual
25 recommended by the mayor as the executive director of the
26 corporation.
27 (b) The executive director:
28 (1) serves at the pleasure of the corporation board; and
29 (2) shall do the following:
30 (A) Administer, manage, and direct the affairs and
31 activities of the corporation and any employees of the
32 corporation in accordance with the policies and under the
33 control and direction of the members of the corporation
34 board.
35 (B) Approve all allowable expenses of the corporation or of
36 any employee or consultant, and expenses incidental to the
37 operation of the corporation.
38 (C) Perform other duties as may be directed by the
39 members of the corporation board in carrying out the
40 purposes of this article.
41 (c) The corporation board shall set the salaries of the executive
42 director and any employees of the corporation.
