9 Chapter 6. Indianapolis Public Education Corporation
10 Operations Fund
11 Sec. 1. The corporation shall create a corporation operations
12 fund to be used by the corporation for the purposes of the
13 corporation.
14 Sec. 2. The corporation operations fund shall be used to deposit
15 revenue received under IC 20-46-8-11.2(j) and IC 20-46-8-12(m).
16 Sec. 3. Expenditures from the corporation operations fund may
17 be made only after appropriation in the annual budget or by an
18 additional appropriation under IC 6-1.1-18-5.
19 Sec. 4. (a) Any balance in the corporation operations fund may
20 be invested in the manner provided for investment of money by a
21 political subdivision. The net proceeds from the investment become
22 a part of the corporation operations fund.
23 (b) Any balance, or a part of the balance, remaining in the
24 corporation operations fund at the end of a year may be retained
25 in the corporation operations fund.
26 Sec. 5. The corporation may use money in the corporation
27 operations fund to carry out the purposes of the corporation.
28 Chapter 7. Indianapolis Public Education Corporation Debt
29 Service Fund
30 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "debt service" includes bonds
31 and coupons, civil bond obligations, lease rental contracts, and
32 interest cost on emergency and temporary loans.
33 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "fund" refers to a debt service
34 fund established under section 3 of this chapter.
35 Sec. 3. The corporation shall establish a debt service fund for
36 purposes of paying the obligations of the corporation.
37 Sec. 4. (a) The debt service fund shall be used to deposit revenue
38 received from the debt service levy imposed under IC 20-46-7 for
39 the purpose of paying all obligations of the corporation.
40 (b) Money in the debt service fund may be used for payment of
41 the following:
42 (1) All debt and other obligations arising out of funds
HB 1423—LS 7118/DI 110

23
1 borrowed or advanced for school buildings when purchased
2 from the proceeds of a bond issue for capital construction.
3 (2) A lease to provide capital construction.
4 (3) Interest on emergency and temporary loans.
5 (4) All debt and other obligations arising out of funds
6 borrowed or advanced for the purchase or lease of school
7 buses when purchased or leased from the proceeds of a bond
8 issue, or from money obtained from a loan made under
9 IC 20-27-4-5, for that purpose.
10 (5) All debt and other obligations arising out of funds
11 borrowed to pay judgments against the corporation.
12 (6) All debt and other obligations arising out of funds
13 borrowed to purchase equipment.
14 Sec. 5. Money in the fund may not be used for payment of debt
15 service, lease payments, or similar obligations for a controlled
16 project that is approved by the voters in a referendum under
17 IC 6-1.1-20.
18 Sec. 6. (a) Lease rental obligations on account of leases entered
19 into under IC 20-47-2 or IC 20-47-3 may be paid by a corporation
