18 lease rental is not fair and reasonable, as the case may be.
19 (c) Upon the filing of a petition under subsection (b), the county
20 auditor shall immediately certify a copy of the petition and any other
21 data that is necessary to present the questions involved to the
22 department of local government finance. Upon receipt of the certified
23 petition and data, if any, the department of local government finance
24 shall fix a date, time, and place for the hearing of the matter, which
25 may not be less than five (5) nor more than thirty (30) days after receipt
26 of the petition and data, if any. The department of local government
27 finance shall:
28 (1) conduct the hearing in the school corporation or corporations,
