HB 1423—LS 7118/DI 110

103
the governing body.
Except as provided in subsection (c), (d), the city-county legislative
body may reduce or modify but not increase a proposed operating and
maintenance budget or tax levy under this section.
(b) (c) The board of each entity listed in subsection (a) (b) shall,
after adoption of its proposed budget and tax levies, submit them, along
with detailed accounts, to the city clerk before September 2.
(c) (d) The city-county legislative body or, when subsection (d) (e)
applies, the fiscal body of an excluded city or town shall review the
